(cpi, power_memory).explanation: CPI and memory power consumption are both outcomes of architectural design choices but CPI does not directly cause changes in memory power consumption;

(cpi, power).explanation: CPI is a performance metric while total power consumption is a physical characteristic, both determined by underlying architectural parameters rather than one causing the other;

(cpi, power_pad).explanation: CPI performance metric does not directly influence pad power consumption, as both are independent outcomes of processor design decisions;
